are you going to take our Daji back

547
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:53,390
to Chongqing

548
00:21:53,390 --> 00:21:54,870
and live with your parents?

549
00:21:54,870 --> 00:21:55,430
Mrs. Dai,

550
00:21:55,430 --> 00:21:56,670
please listen to me.

551
00:21:56,980 --> 00:21:58,150
What I mean is,

552
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,720
wherever the kids want to live,
that's up to them.

553
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,540
For now, we thought

554
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:04,120
that apartment could temporarily
serve as their marital house.

555
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:05,950
Why don't you just
sell the place in Chongqing?

556
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:07,110
Wouldn't that cover the cost?

557
00:22:09,980 --> 00:22:10,780
Mrs. Dai,

558
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:13,910
I just don't think it's right

559
00:22:14,220 --> 00:22:16,020
to ask my parents to sell
the home they bought

560
00:22:16,020 --> 00:22:18,220
for retirement just because
Daji and I need a place to live.

561
00:22:18,220 --> 00:22:19,280
Let me tell you something,

562
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:20,910
marriage isn't just
between the two of you.

563
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:22,910
It's between two families.

564
00:22:22,910 --> 00:22:24,110
And right now, I've sold

565
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:25,870
all the property I had
for my own retirement

566
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:27,190
just to support Daji.

567
00:22:27,390 --> 00:22:28,190
Mom...

568
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:31,220
- Mrs. Dai, let me do the maths for you.
- Just sell the place in Chongqing.

569
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:33,300
Look, our company
is doing well overall right now.

570
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:34,980
If we can land a big project,

571
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:37,190
for a 1.5 million yuan apartment plus...

572
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:38,540
Zhou Shui!

573
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:41,560
Since when do you think you can
come here and crunch numbers with me?

574
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:42,780
Mrs. Dai, I wasn't trying to...

575
00:22:42,780 --> 00:22:43,670
Alright, that's enough.

576
00:22:44,060 --> 00:22:45,720
I raised my daughter
through thick and thin,

577
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:48,000
and now you think it's your
place to talk to me about numbers?

578
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,040
He didn't mean it like that.

579
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:49,910
Then what did he mean?

580
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:51,020
Go on, explain it to me.

581
00:22:51,020 --> 00:22:51,440
Zhou Shui,

582
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,300
what did you say when you came
to our house a few years ago?

583
00:22:54,980 --> 00:22:57,110
You asked for two years

584
00:22:57,260 --> 00:22:58,780
to give Daji a home,

585
00:22:58,780 --> 00:22:59,780
to buy her an apartment.

586
00:22:59,780 --> 00:23:01,060
Now all these years have passed,

587
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:02,630
have you kept your promise?

588
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,500
Let me tell you,

589
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:07,500
a real man takes responsibility.

590
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:09,390
If you make a promise,
you follow through.

591
00:23:09,390 --> 00:23:09,910
Zhou Shui

592
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:11,950
isn't just making empty promises.

593
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:13,910
He means what he says,
he is responsible.

594
00:23:13,910 --> 00:23:15,590
And how exactly is he
taking responsibility?

595
00:23:16,020 --> 00:23:17,830
Is this all just talk?

596
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:19,060
Mrs. Dai...

597
00:23:19,430 --> 00:23:20,640
Let's just sit down

598
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:21,830
and talk this through calmly.

599
00:23:21,980 --> 00:23:23,280
So what you're really saying is,

600
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:25,400
you're not going to sell
your apartment in Chongqing

601
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,600
to buy a place here in Beijing,

602
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:27,430
is that it?

603
00:23:27,430 --> 00:23:27,910
Mrs. Dai,

604
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:29,630
we will buy a place in Beijing,
I promise.

605
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:31,060
Enough! Don't say another word.

606
00:23:31,060 --> 00:23:31,920
That's not what he...

607
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:32,430
Dad!

608
00:23:35,780 --> 00:23:39,780
You can't expect us
to buy a place in Beijing

609
00:23:40,350 --> 00:23:41,640
just because you sold your home,

610
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:42,400
and then turn around

611
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:45,220
and expect my parents to sell the
home they bought for retirement too.

612
00:23:45,220 --> 00:23:46,080
That's not fair, is it?

613
00:23:46,260 --> 00:23:47,150
Shut up!

614
00:23:50,390 --> 00:23:51,150
Zhou Shui.

615
00:23:51,150 --> 00:23:52,190
Zhou Shui, don't say that.

616
00:23:52,190 --> 00:23:53,590
Are you listening to yourself?

617
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:55,700
I can live in a retirement home.

618
00:23:55,870 --> 00:23:58,300
I can sell my house
because I want to support my daughter.

619
00:23:58,500 --> 00:23:59,360
And your parents can't?

620
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,480
Wow. You've really got it
all worked out, haven't you?

621
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:03,840
What a clever little plan,
slapped me right in the face with it.

622
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,480
Forget it. We're not
getting married anymore.

623
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:06,560
Let's just forget about it.

624
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,590
Forget about it, huh?

625
00:24:19,740 --> 00:24:20,540
Zhou Shui,

626
00:24:21,430 --> 00:24:23,060
is that what you wanted to hear?

627
00:24:23,590 --> 00:24:25,220
Is that how you really feel?

628
00:24:25,220 --> 00:24:26,320
Mrs. Dai, I never said that.

629
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:29,000
I've always wanted to marry Daji.
When it comes to buying a place...

630
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,160
Then it must be your father
who doesn't want this marriage.

631
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:33,680
That's not true. I do want them
to get married. As soon as possible.

632
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:36,080
Then why won't you contribute
some money to buy a house for them?

633
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:36,880
Mom, stop. Just stop.

634
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:37,240
Let's go.

635
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:37,760
Why won't you?

636
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:38,240
Please stop.

637
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:40,630
You keep saying you want to get married,
but when it comes time

638
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:42,780
to actually step up, there's nothing.

639
00:24:42,780 --> 00:24:45,060
My daughter gave you
eight years of her life.

640
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:46,500
And in the end, she got nothing.

641
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,020
Not even a real promise.

642
00:24:48,670 --> 00:24:49,870
This marriage isn't happening.

643
00:24:50,020 --> 00:24:51,060
It's over.

644
00:24:51,060 --> 00:24:51,780
Let's go.

645
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:54,430
We're just going to step outside
and cool off for a bit. Sorry.

646
00:24:55,630 --> 00:24:58,390
Don't get worked up so easily.

647
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:21,590
That mother-in-law of yours

648
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,980
has got one fiery temper.

649
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:27,390
Kid,

650
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:29,700
you're really in for it down the line.

651
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:33,830
There you go again.

652
00:25:33,830 --> 00:25:34,540
Seriously.

653
00:25:34,540 --> 00:25:36,190
You're not pretty when you're mad,

654
00:25:36,190 --> 00:25:37,260
you know that?

655
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:38,590
Come on, don't be angry anymore.

656
00:25:38,590 --> 00:25:40,840
Forget about that nonsense.
You think I'm joking with you?

657
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:43,430
Owning a home is one of the most
important things in a woman's life.

658
00:25:43,430 --> 00:25:45,480
It's your sense of security.
Do you understand that?

659
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,260
I know.

660
00:25:46,260 --> 00:25:47,260
You're right.

661
00:25:47,260 --> 00:25:48,350
I get it.

662
00:25:48,740 --> 00:25:49,590
But think about it,

663
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:50,190
his dad,

664
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:50,950
he just got here,

665
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:53,950
and right away you're already fighting

666
00:25:53,950 --> 00:25:54,630
with him.

667
00:25:54,740 --> 00:25:56,020
That's not easy for them either.

668
00:25:56,040 --> 00:25:58,640
His parents are doing the best they can,
with what little they have.

669
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,950
They run this tiny hotpot place,

670
00:26:00,110 --> 00:26:01,540
and they've worked their whole lives

671
00:26:01,630 --> 00:26:03,540
just to afford a small apartment
in the city.

672
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:05,110
That's their retirement home.

673
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:07,020
If they sell it,
how are they supposed to live?

674
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:08,870
Why are you feeling sorry for them?

675
00:26:11,740 --> 00:26:12,630
Tell me,

676
00:26:13,980 --> 00:26:15,430
do you love Daji?

677
00:26:15,870 --> 00:26:16,670
Of course I do.

678
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:19,950
Do you really want to marry her?

679
00:26:24,300 --> 00:26:25,110
Good.

680
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:29,590
Then we have to contribute
the money. It's worth it.

681
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:31,950
Mom, I'm your daughter.

682
00:26:31,950 --> 00:26:33,160
Of course I care about you too.

683
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:35,520
You just said it out of the blue
that you're selling your house.

684
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:36,540
Where would you even live?

685
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,830
I'll move into a nursing home.

686
00:26:39,430 --> 00:26:40,220
Oh my God.

687
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:41,160
Is this necessary?

688
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,430
You have a perfectly good house,

689
00:26:42,430 --> 00:26:44,040
but you'd rather live in a nursing home.

690
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:46,000
Think about it,
if we spend all the money

691
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:48,060
just to cover a down payment,
is it really worth it?

692
00:26:48,060 --> 00:26:48,780
Right?

693
00:26:49,020 --> 00:26:51,460
Right now we're finally living
a little more comfortably,

694
00:26:51,670 --> 00:26:52,600
and then on top of that

695
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,500
we'll have to start paying
a mortgage every month.

696
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:56,120
Just stop and think
about it for a second.

697
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:56,560
He's a man.

698
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,870
He says he loves you,
but when it comes time to buy a home,

699
00:26:58,870 --> 00:27:00,540
he shrinks away like a coward.

700
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:02,220
You tell me, is that really love?

701
00:27:03,590 --> 00:27:06,830
But Dad, if you sell the apartment,

702
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,300
where are you and Mom going to live?

703
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:10,880
The old house back home isn't livable.

704
00:27:14,540 --> 00:27:17,430
When I get back, I'll put
the apartment up for sale.

705
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:22,300
And I'll transfer the hotpot shop
to someone else too.

706
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:27,120
Your mom and I will move back
to our hometown.

707
00:27:30,700 --> 00:27:32,150
We're getting up there in age.

708
00:27:33,390 --> 00:27:34,630
We can live anywhere.

709
00:27:35,460 --> 00:27:36,950
And that house back home,

710
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:38,870
once we fix it up a bit,

711
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:40,220
it'll be just fine.

712
00:27:44,260 --> 00:27:46,220
Daji's been with you for so many years.

713
00:27:47,780 --> 00:27:49,540
You owe her a proper future.

714
00:27:59,390 --> 00:28:00,430
Shichahai...

715
00:28:01,630 --> 00:28:02,670
Shichahai...

716
00:28:05,020 --> 00:28:06,630
Shichahai...

717
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:09,910
You're so small.

718
00:28:11,020 --> 00:28:13,390
Can you even really be called a "sea"?

719
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,390
In Beijing,

720
00:28:17,150 --> 00:28:18,220
this is the sea.

721
00:28:20,260 --> 00:28:22,260
But when will little shrimp like us

722
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:25,020
ever get to swim in the sea?

723
00:28:26,260 --> 00:28:28,830
Aren't we already swimming in it?

724
00:28:41,390 --> 00:28:41,980
Is she asleep?

725
00:28:50,590 --> 00:28:52,870
Did you talk to your dad?

726
00:28:53,020 --> 00:28:54,110
What did he say?

727
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:57,190
He'll sell the apartment.

728
00:28:57,740 --> 00:28:58,260
Wait,

729
00:28:59,670 --> 00:29:02,670
your parents are selling their home,
and my mom wants to sell hers too,

730
00:29:02,780 --> 00:29:04,630
all just to scrape together
a down payment?

731
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:08,260
It's so ridiculous.

732
00:29:08,870 --> 00:29:11,300
Why are we suddenly getting married?

733
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:14,300
And suddenly needing to buy
a multi-million yuan apartment?

734
00:29:15,460 --> 00:29:16,260
It's insane.

735
00:29:16,430 --> 00:29:17,630
Do you not want to get married?

736
00:29:18,780 --> 00:29:19,980
Is that a gray hair?

737
00:29:20,260 --> 00:29:20,780
Look here.

738
00:29:20,780 --> 00:29:22,500
This one, is it?

739
00:29:22,670 --> 00:29:23,540
It really is.

740
00:29:24,190 --> 00:29:24,760
Don't pull it.

741
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,740
They say if you pull one,
more will grow.

742
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:30,920
If we add up everything we have now,
including what the company's worth,

743
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:32,500
how much do we have?

744
00:29:35,430 --> 00:29:37,060
About 570 or 580 thousand.

745
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:38,020
So basically,

746
00:29:39,220 --> 00:29:42,740
if we don't sell our parents' homes
and rely just on what we've got,

747
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,680
we're still short almost
a million for the down payment.

748
00:29:46,110 --> 00:29:46,910
A million...

749
00:29:55,540 --> 00:29:56,350
Hi, Mao!

750
00:29:56,780 --> 00:29:57,590
Hi, Shui!

751
00:29:58,020 --> 00:29:59,390
So, what's up?

752
00:29:59,950 --> 00:30:00,950
Oh, nothing really.

753
00:30:02,430 --> 00:30:03,390
What are you up to?

754
00:30:04,540 --> 00:30:05,910
Same old, same old.

755
00:30:06,110 --> 00:30:07,700
Why? Got some orders for me?

756
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:09,190
No orders.

757
00:30:09,190 --> 00:30:10,060
I just...

758
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,590
You're free to talk, right?

759
00:30:12,590 --> 00:30:14,020
I need to ask you something.

760
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:15,830
Yeah, I can talk.

761
00:30:16,540 --> 00:30:17,350
Shui,

762
00:30:17,780 --> 00:30:19,390
are you and Daji making a movie?

763
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:22,350
I knew it!

764
00:30:22,950 --> 00:30:23,950
You brat!

765
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:25,430
You used to say

766
00:30:25,780 --> 00:30:27,780
that if you ever got the chance
to make a movie,

767
00:30:27,780 --> 00:30:29,260
you'd get us Five Useless Misfits

768
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:30,460
back together.

769
00:30:30,540 --> 00:30:31,830
I've been waiting for this day,

770
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:32,540
you know?

771
00:30:32,540 --> 00:30:33,260
Mao,

772
00:30:34,190 --> 00:30:35,460
I'm not calling about a movie.

773
00:30:36,150 --> 00:30:37,110
Not a movie?

774
00:30:38,020 --> 00:30:39,110
Then what's up?

775
00:30:49,980 --> 00:30:53,400
"Wishing a successful start
to Fallen Angels: Yanjiao Edition!"

776
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:55,540
I've asked you out so many times
and you've ignored me.

777
00:30:55,740 --> 00:30:57,060
So what brings you here today?

778
00:30:58,040 --> 00:30:59,720
Don't tell me you're here
to borrow money?

779
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,480
You're really here to borrow money?

780
00:31:07,780 --> 00:31:08,300
Yes.

781
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:11,430
Zhou Shui and I are
planning to get married.

782
00:31:11,700 --> 00:31:12,540
Congratulations.

783
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:15,350
I always knew you two were meant

784
00:31:15,350 --> 00:31:16,780
to have the perfect ending.

785
00:31:18,910 --> 00:31:20,950
I'm not sure about
the "perfect ending" part,

786
00:31:21,430 --> 00:31:23,350
but right now, we need to buy a place.

787
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,500
We're still short about
a million for the down payment.

788
00:31:26,220 --> 00:31:27,390
Can you help us?

789
00:31:29,260 --> 00:31:30,220
You mean cash?

790
00:31:33,670 --> 00:31:34,950
I don't have any cash.

791
00:31:36,590 --> 00:31:37,390
Liao only

792
00:31:37,540 --> 00:31:39,300
gave me cards I can use to buy things.

793
00:31:39,590 --> 00:31:42,350
They're with the driver.
I can't even withdraw money from them.

794
00:31:44,590 --> 00:31:45,390
To be honest,

795
00:31:45,980 --> 00:31:46,950
I don't think I even

796
00:31:46,950 --> 00:31:48,260
have enough to buy a plane ticket.

797
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:52,430
Why?

798
00:31:53,110 --> 00:31:54,430
Is he afraid you'll run away?

799
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:02,430
From here,

800
00:32:03,430 --> 00:32:04,670
it doesn't look that tall.

801
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:06,670
Liao had someone check
it out when he bought it.

802
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:10,150
They said it faced a mountain
from the front door. Good feng shui.

803
00:32:12,590 --> 00:32:14,980
What about you? Do you think it's good?

804
00:32:18,060 --> 00:32:20,540
The good feng shui, the fancy furniture,

805
00:32:22,020 --> 00:32:23,540
none of it really belongs to me.

806
00:32:25,190 --> 00:32:26,590
Liao never gives me actual money.

807
00:32:28,190 --> 00:32:29,590
He just gives me

808
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:31,350
the illusion that I'm wealthy.

809
00:32:33,390 --> 00:32:34,700
Jingshu, I'm sorry

810
00:32:35,670 --> 00:32:37,430
for asking for money
as soon as I saw you.

811
00:32:38,910 --> 00:32:40,430
I shouldn't have done that.

812
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,800
Let's go get some
beauty treatments later.

813
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:48,020
There's a new medical
aesthetics clinic in CWTC.

814
00:32:48,020 --> 00:32:48,780
We can use my card.

815
00:32:51,190 --> 00:32:52,430
Jingshu, I can't today.

816
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:54,960
I've got to head back for
a meeting this afternoon.

817
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:56,080
The client's been rushing us.

818
00:32:57,260 --> 00:32:58,220
Go without me.

819
00:32:59,260 --> 00:33:01,260
Let's do this another time.

820
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:06,440
Another time is just a nice way
of saying it's never going to happen.

821
00:33:16,150 --> 00:33:17,060
Your apartment is

822
00:33:17,060 --> 00:33:18,540
worth quite a lot, isn't it?

823
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:21,190
Why don't you just sell it?

824
00:33:22,700 --> 00:33:24,260
Or maybe mortgage it,

825
00:33:24,260 --> 00:33:25,260
pull out some cash,

826
00:33:25,260 --> 00:33:26,630
and then just run.

827
00:33:28,500 --> 00:33:30,460
You know what?
I've actually thought about that.

828
00:33:35,540 --> 00:33:36,430
You're laughing?

829
00:33:38,260 --> 00:33:39,540
Really?

830
00:33:42,630 --> 00:33:43,670
I'm trying to tell you,

831
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:46,500
youth doesn't last.

832
00:33:47,500 --> 00:33:48,540
Beauty doesn't last.

833
00:33:50,430 --> 00:33:53,350
You need to hold on to something that
gives you real power, real security.

834
00:33:55,350 --> 00:33:56,190
Got it?

835
00:34:05,260 --> 00:34:06,670
Got it, Daji.

836
00:34:08,750 --> 00:34:10,020
You really care about me.

837
00:34:24,140 --> 00:34:25,230
Hey, Liao.

838
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:27,430
I wanted to ask for a favor.

839
00:34:27,950 --> 00:34:30,500
About the ad campaign for our
new property development,

840
00:34:30,500 --> 00:34:32,460
could you let a friend
of mine handle it?

841
00:34:33,230 --> 00:34:35,100
What friend?

842
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,980
She's like a big sister to me.

843
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:40,160
She's going through
a tough time with her business.

844
00:34:40,160 --> 00:34:41,350
I really want to help her out.

845
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:43,660
Haven't I told you

846
00:34:43,660 --> 00:34:45,910
not to get involved in
my business affairs?

847
00:34:48,790 --> 00:34:50,460
I'm only asking this one time.

848
00:34:51,180 --> 00:34:52,390
Just do it for me,

849
00:34:52,390 --> 00:34:53,100
okay?

850
00:34:53,830 --> 00:34:55,460
And what about that
thing I asked you for?

851
00:34:55,950 --> 00:34:57,180
Have you made up your mind?

852
00:34:59,580 --> 00:35:00,980
You asked me for something,

853
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,580
and now I'm asking you for something.

854
00:35:05,580 --> 00:35:07,020
I just want a son.

855
00:35:29,350 --> 00:35:29,950
What?

856
00:35:30,020 --> 00:35:30,870
What's going on?

857
00:35:32,310 --> 00:35:33,060
What happened?

858
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:34,980
Our lives are about to change,
big times!

859
00:35:34,980 --> 00:35:35,680
What do you mean?

860
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:38,390
A real estate tycoon just reached
out to us to do an ad campaign.

861
00:35:38,390 --> 00:35:40,460
The budget is two million.

862
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:42,790
That's a lot!

863
00:35:42,790 --> 00:35:44,500
Hang on, hang on.

864
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:46,060
No middlemen taking a cut?

865
00:35:46,100 --> 00:35:46,910
No.

866
00:35:47,060 --> 00:35:48,270
Hold on,

867
00:35:48,310 --> 00:35:50,100
how did you even land a gig like this?

868
00:35:50,620 --> 00:35:51,660
He just showed up,

869
00:35:52,270 --> 00:35:53,580
came straight to us himself.

870
00:35:54,140 --> 00:35:54,660
No way!

871
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:57,270
If we're smart with the budget,
we could pocket a million easy.

872
00:35:57,430 --> 00:35:58,020
We're good.

873
00:35:58,020 --> 00:35:59,120
You're getting a raise, Yu!

874
00:35:59,180 --> 00:35:59,950
Thanks, Shui!

875
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:02,120
Let's get to work!

876
00:36:03,430 --> 00:36:04,180
Daji,

877
00:36:04,230 --> 00:36:05,580
if we really make that million,

878
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:07,100
can I borrow a little?

879
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:10,180
You know how it is with artists,
we're always broke,

880
00:36:10,180 --> 00:36:12,060
and we owe our girlfriends
a ton of money.

881
00:36:12,060 --> 00:36:13,140
Shameless!

882
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:14,460
But I like it.

883
00:36:14,620 --> 00:36:16,870
Because I love investing in artists,

884
00:36:16,910 --> 00:36:19,230
especially the handsome ones like you.

885
00:36:21,160 --> 00:36:23,270
I really don't want my parents
to sell their apartment,

886
00:36:23,790 --> 00:36:25,830
but I promised your mom
we'd buy a place in Beijing.

887
00:36:25,830 --> 00:36:27,020
If we don't,

888
00:36:27,060 --> 00:36:29,540
she'll come charging back
from Ezhou and chop me in half.

889
00:36:29,540 --> 00:36:30,230
Alright.

890
00:36:30,910 --> 00:36:31,580
No problem.

891
00:36:31,660 --> 00:36:32,620
I'll lend it to you.

892
00:36:33,020 --> 00:36:33,830
How much do you need?

893
00:36:33,910 --> 00:36:34,710
One million.

894
00:36:35,430 --> 00:36:36,790
Come on, that's all I have!

895
00:36:36,830 --> 00:36:37,000
I...

896
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:38,230
Keep your eyes on the road!

897
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:38,680
My phone.

898
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,360
- You...
- Come on.

899
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:39,870
It's ringing.

900
00:36:39,870 --> 00:36:40,760
Someone's calling me.

901
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:41,200
Fine, fine.

902
00:36:41,200 --> 00:36:41,980
Hello.

903
00:36:44,060 --> 00:36:44,870
This is Zhou Shui.

904
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:47,460
You want me to make a movie?

905
00:36:49,870 --> 00:36:51,960
Dude, let me give you some advice.

906
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:54,160
Turn yourself in. It's not
too late to do the right thing.

907
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,280
Taking advantage of someone's dream
to scam their money

908
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:58,500
is the lowest, most shameless
thing you can do. Got it?

909
00:36:59,430 --> 00:36:59,960
Who was that?

910
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:02,800
Remember when I first came to Beijing

911
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:04,880
and someone said they wanted
to make a movie with me?

912
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:06,720
In the end, they scammed me
out of all my money.

913
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:07,760
It's another one of those.

914
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:08,390
Another scammer?

915
00:37:09,750 --> 00:37:12,200
After all these years,
they're still using the same script.

916
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:13,950
"I'd like to offer you a chance."

917
00:37:14,950 --> 00:37:16,910
I'm not falling into
the same trap twice.

918
00:37:17,790 --> 00:37:19,180
Did he say his name?

919
00:37:19,180 --> 00:37:20,270
Which company?

920
00:37:21,430 --> 00:37:23,270
Something like Ruidi Pictures.

921
00:37:23,580 --> 00:37:24,830
His name is Man something.

922
00:37:24,830 --> 00:37:25,430
Can't remember.

923
00:37:25,430 --> 00:37:26,350
Man Jiaxin!

924
00:37:26,790 --> 00:37:27,980
Yeah! How'd you know?

925
00:37:27,980 --> 00:37:29,230
It was Man Jiaxin?

926
00:37:31,020 --> 00:37:32,180
Who doesn't know that name?

927
00:37:32,180 --> 00:37:34,430
The one and only producer, Man Jiaxin!

928
00:37:34,910 --> 00:37:35,910
He's real?

929
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:36,710
Of course he's real!

930
00:37:36,710 --> 00:37:38,640
Have you been living under a rock?
Look him up.

931
00:37:39,080 --> 00:37:39,580
(Beacon Camp)

932
00:37:39,580 --> 00:37:40,580
Take a look.

933
00:37:40,580 --> 00:37:41,620
These are my works.

934
00:37:42,830 --> 00:37:43,980
Do you believe me now?

935
00:37:45,140 --> 00:37:46,270
I really like this one.

936
00:37:46,580 --> 00:37:47,750
That's Mr. Bai's work.

937
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:51,180
I was being overly cautious before.
Sorry about that.

938
00:37:51,750 --> 00:37:53,040
No worries. Let's get to business.

939
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:54,840
You wrote the script for
Such A Good Love, right?

940
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:56,140
Come on.

941
00:37:58,350 --> 00:37:58,950
I wrote it.

942
00:37:58,950 --> 00:38:01,270
But that was from a long time ago.

943
00:38:01,390 --> 00:38:02,830
They sent the script to me.

944
00:38:03,980 --> 00:38:06,870
As soon as I read it,
I knew it'd be a hit.

945
00:38:07,230 --> 00:38:08,750
So we'd like to work with you.

946
00:38:09,230 --> 00:38:10,100
How?

947
00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:12,950
We want you to direct the film.

948
00:38:13,390 --> 00:38:15,270
We're looking at

949
00:38:15,430 --> 00:38:17,310
a preliminary investment of 20 million.

950
00:38:17,790 --> 00:38:18,950
20 million...

951
00:38:22,230 --> 00:38:24,710
If we turned that 20 million into cash

952
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:25,720
and tossed it off here,

953
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,310
do you think it'd crush the cars below?

954
00:38:27,310 --> 00:38:27,980
Definitely.

955
00:38:29,460 --> 00:38:30,270
Daji,

956
00:38:30,830 --> 00:38:33,350
are we really really making a
film with a 20 million investment?

957
00:38:33,430 --> 00:38:35,870
We're making a film with
a 20 million investment!

958
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:38,430
Period. Exclamation point.

959
00:38:39,310 --> 00:38:40,710
How long have we been in Beijing?

960
00:38:40,980 --> 00:38:42,500
Nine years.

961
00:38:43,230 --> 00:38:45,310
And now we're finally making a movie.

962
00:38:45,950 --> 00:38:48,140
Who was it, way back then,

963
00:38:48,140 --> 00:38:50,100
who said you'd shine one day?

964
00:38:50,310 --> 00:38:51,350
Was I wrong?

965
00:38:52,020 --> 00:38:53,230
You were right, Daji.

966
00:38:53,580 --> 00:38:55,620
The Scandalous Couple is making a movie!

967
00:38:55,980 --> 00:38:58,500
We're making a movie!

968
00:38:58,620 --> 00:39:00,580
Look, it's October now.

969
00:39:00,580 --> 00:39:01,430
The latest we can

970
00:39:01,430 --> 00:39:03,390
deliver the ad is the end of November.

971
00:39:03,390 --> 00:39:04,200
So during that time,

972
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:05,840
you can work on
revising the movie script.

973
00:39:06,750 --> 00:39:09,430
Shooting the ad
and rewriting the script?

974
00:39:09,580 --> 00:39:11,710
My brain is gonna explode!

975
00:39:12,560 --> 00:39:14,540
How about this,
I'll handle the script revisions.

976
00:39:14,540 --> 00:39:16,310
You just focus on
finishing the ad shoot.

977
00:39:16,310 --> 00:39:18,600
When that's done,
you're going straight into the film crew.

978
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:20,660
Let Yu take over post-production.

979
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:21,840
- You got it?
- Yes.

980
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:23,120
No room for mistakes, alright?

981
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:23,320
Okay.

982
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,920
But when it's time
to meet with the client,

983
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:26,400
you two definitely need to be there.

984
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,140
They're hiring you.

985
00:39:27,140 --> 00:39:28,750
We'll figure that out
when the time comes.

986
00:39:29,830 --> 00:39:31,580
How long do you think
post-production will take?

987
00:39:32,430 --> 00:39:33,180
Post?

988
00:39:33,180 --> 00:39:34,200
About a month and a half.

989
00:39:34,580 --> 00:39:35,750
About a month and a half.

990
00:39:36,100 --> 00:39:37,870
November... January.

991
00:39:37,870 --> 00:39:38,980
Mid-January.

992
00:39:40,540 --> 00:39:41,460
That'll work!

993
00:39:41,460 --> 00:39:41,960
Yeah!

994
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:43,750
We start filming the movie
on February 15th.

995
00:39:43,750 --> 00:39:45,270
We've got more than enough time!

996
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:46,790
Okay.

997
00:39:46,790 --> 00:39:47,660
- We can do this.
- Okay.

998
00:39:47,830 --> 00:39:48,580
Is that my phone?

999
00:39:48,710 --> 00:39:49,180
Yes.

1000
00:39:49,310 --> 00:39:50,750
I have to answer it. Excuse me.

1001
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:55,310
Hello.

1002
00:39:55,660 --> 00:39:56,500
This is she.

1003
00:39:57,980 --> 00:39:59,950
Let's drop the medium shot.

1004
00:39:59,980 --> 00:40:01,950
The wide shot's just too
time-consuming this way.

1005
00:40:02,060 --> 00:40:02,790
Are you certain?

1006
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:06,140
Hang on, I'm sure we
can work something out.

1007
00:40:06,140 --> 00:40:06,830
Okay?

1008
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:09,910
Alright. Thank you.

1009
00:40:12,390 --> 00:40:13,180
What's going on?

1010
00:40:16,620 --> 00:40:18,430
I just got a call from
Fortune Real Estate.

1011
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,180
The development we're
supposed to shoot for,

1012
00:40:20,180 --> 00:40:21,360
the completion's been delayed.

1013
00:40:21,390 --> 00:40:23,180
They want to push the ad shoot

1014
00:40:23,180 --> 00:40:24,910
to February 16th.

1015
00:40:25,660 --> 00:40:26,950
February 16th?

1016
00:40:26,950 --> 00:40:27,580
Yes.

1017
00:40:27,640 --> 00:40:29,840
But aren't you guys starting
the film shoot on the 15th?

1018
00:40:29,980 --> 00:40:30,540
Yes.

1019
00:40:30,660 --> 00:40:32,310
Then who's going to shoot the ad?

1020
00:40:42,390 --> 00:40:43,430
Push back the start date?

1021
00:40:43,980 --> 00:40:44,910
Are you kidding me?

1022
00:40:45,660 --> 00:40:46,580
Absolutely not.

1023
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:48,460
The actors' contracts are signed.

1024
00:40:48,750 --> 00:40:50,660
We have to start shooting
on February 15th.

1025
00:40:51,430 --> 00:40:52,060
Mr. Man,

1026
00:40:52,750 --> 00:40:54,100
just give us one week.

1027
00:40:54,100 --> 00:40:55,500
Not even a day.

1028
00:40:56,350 --> 00:40:57,360
These are big-name actors.

1029
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,400
It was hard enough getting them
to clear their schedules

1030
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:00,710
for a brand-new director like you.

1031
00:41:01,180 --> 00:41:02,460
How am I supposed to explain this?

1032
00:41:03,020 --> 00:41:05,240
"Sorry, our director needs to
go shoot a commercial first"?

1033
00:41:05,910 --> 00:41:07,140
What's more important,

1034
00:41:07,500 --> 00:41:10,580
the ad or the film?

1035
00:41:10,950 --> 00:41:12,350
The director's fee might not be much,

1036
00:41:12,580 --> 00:41:14,100
but this is a huge opportunity for you.

1037
00:41:14,230 --> 00:41:15,790
If you insist on doing the ad,

1038
00:41:16,310 --> 00:41:17,710
you can forget about the film then.

1039
00:41:19,790 --> 00:41:20,390
Mr. Man...

1040
00:41:23,020 --> 00:41:23,710
He hanged up.

1041
00:41:24,710 --> 00:41:25,500
Alright then.

1042
00:41:26,060 --> 00:41:27,020
There's no other way.

1043
00:41:27,230 --> 00:41:28,620
We have to decide,

1044
00:41:29,270 --> 00:41:31,140
the movie or the ad?

1045
00:41:31,180 --> 00:41:33,310
Do we choose our dream or a home?

1046
00:41:34,660 --> 00:41:35,750
What's your decision?

1047
00:41:50,140 --> 00:41:51,000
Let me think about it.

1048
00:41:54,100 --> 00:41:55,100
You said it yourself,

1049
00:41:55,500 --> 00:41:57,790
in moments like this,
you've got to follow your gut.

1050
00:41:58,980 --> 00:42:00,830
Before this red light turns green,

1051
00:42:01,270 --> 00:42:02,390
I want your answer.

1052
00:42:15,750 --> 00:42:16,980
How about you take the ad,

1053
00:42:17,350 --> 00:42:18,500
and I shoot the film?

1054
00:42:18,790 --> 00:42:21,230
Shameless. You've got ten seconds left.

1055
00:42:31,790 --> 00:42:33,580
Then I'll shoot the ad,
and you do the movie.

1056
00:42:33,660 --> 00:42:34,180
Eight seconds.

1057
00:42:34,180 --> 00:42:35,600
No way. Such A Good Love is our story.

1058
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:37,620
If we shoot it, we shoot it together.
Six seconds.

1059
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:44,620
But if we really go all-in
on this movie,

1060
00:42:44,620 --> 00:42:45,870
we won't have money for a place.

1061
00:42:45,870 --> 00:42:47,870
And without a home,
how do we get married? Four.

1062
00:42:47,950 --> 00:42:49,100
You're overthinking it.

1063
00:42:49,100 --> 00:42:49,910
Last two seconds.

1064
00:42:49,910 --> 00:42:51,390
Just follow your heart.

1065
00:42:51,390 --> 00:42:52,790
Whatever you choose, go with that.

1066
00:43:37,470 --> 00:43:38,810
♪Is it worth it?♪

1067
00:43:39,050 --> 00:43:42,820
♪From having nothing to having nothing♪

1068
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:45,900
♪Is it worth it?♪

1069
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:50,140
♪To turn back at every crossroads♪

1070
00:43:51,700 --> 00:43:52,750
♪Is it worth it?♪

1071
00:43:53,320 --> 00:43:57,110
♪Swearing to become the sea,
not just a river♪

1072
00:43:58,560 --> 00:43:59,980
♪Is it worth it?♪

1073
00:44:00,460 --> 00:44:04,570
♪That night,
the wine was finished with just one sip♪

1074
00:44:05,610 --> 00:44:07,280
♪Do you dare?♪

1075
00:44:07,440 --> 00:44:11,230
♪When having nothing, I don't frown♪

1076
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:14,270
♪Do you dare?♪

1077
00:44:14,350 --> 00:44:18,620
♪Once I decide to start,
I hold your hand tightly♪

1078
00:44:19,630 --> 00:44:21,550
♪Do you dare?♪

1079
00:44:21,620 --> 00:44:25,160
♪Even in the coldest winter,
we feel it on the ice♪

1080
00:44:26,820 --> 00:44:28,490
♪Do you dare?♪

1081
00:44:28,590 --> 00:44:32,720
♪Striving for an outlet
in reality and love♪

1082
00:44:34,080 --> 00:44:39,310
♪Only to realize when we drift apart♪

1083
00:44:39,390 --> 00:44:44,350
♪We mistook that day for forever♪

1084
